                     <interp inst="t17691018-1-person35" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to the prosecutor. Those things are his property; I know them by often seeing them, as well as by our private mark on the spoons. I was present when some things were found; some upon the prisoner, and some in his box.</p>
               <p>Q. How old is the prisoner?</p>
               <p>Branston. He is about fifteen or sixteen years of age.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I saw the things lying about, and I took them up.</p>
